by this underhanded law -- and
also that other

12:26.079 --> 12:30.984 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
clinics would be able to reopen.
You know,
one of the things that happened
with HB-2

12:31.017 --> 12:35.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was that it devastated abortion
access in
Texas, closing half of the laws,
under which

12:35.989 --> 12:40.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Supreme Court said today was
unconstitutional,
because they weren't justified
on medical

12:40.226 --> 12:41.961 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
grounds at all.

12:41.995 --> 12:44.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: So, Steven Aden,
what worked and
what didn't in your argument to
keep those

12:44.764 --> 12:48.901 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
-- or try to limit the scope of
the abortion
clinics?

12:48.935 --> 12:50.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN ADEN, Alliance Defending
Freedom: Well,
we believe, of course, that it's
a very big

12:50.937 --> 12:54.507 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
disappointment and a big loss
for women's
health and safety.

12:54.540 --> 12:59.579 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All Texas was trying to do was
regulate abortion
in the same way and same manner
as other similar

12:59.612 --> 13:04.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
outpatient abortion procedures.
If you or
I go in for a colonoscopy or a
laparoscopy,

13:04.584 --> 13:09.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
chances are very good that our
doctor will
have admitting privileges,
because once in

13:09.122 --> 13:13.393 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a while, something goes wrong.
And when something
goes wrong, you want the best
standard of

13:13.426 --> 13:15.395 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
health care available to help
you.

13:15.428 --> 13:19.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's all that Texas was
trying to do.
And the fact that the Supreme
Court would

13:19.065 --> 13:24.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
strike this law down by one
vote, which it
did, doesn't augur well,
unfortunately, for

13:24.137 --> 13:25.772 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
women's health.

13:25.805 --> 13:27.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Weren't you hoping
more for a
4-4 let it stand ruling, rather
than...

13:27.874 --> 13:31.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN ADEN: That would have
been the result,
that's right, Gwen. If Justice
Kennedy had

13:31.244 --> 13:35.515 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
come along, it would have been a
4-4 split,
and the good Fifth Circuit
decision affirming

13:35.548 --> 13:38.184 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the laws would have been upheld.
But, alas,
that didn't happen today.

13:38.217 --> 13:41.354 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Nancy Northup, what
about this
argument that this was something
affecting

13:41.387 --> 13:44.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
women's health and in fact that
the law was
designed to protect women's
health?

13:44.624 --> 13:49.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NANCY NORTHUP: Well, I think the
Supreme Court
made clear today that this was a
pretext,

13:49.762 --> 13:54.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the idea that it was about
women's health,
because, as the American Medical
Association

13:54.934 --> 13:56.869 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and others saw, it didn't
advance women's
health.

13:56.903 --> 14:01.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in fact it hurt it by
putting so many
women out of reach of being able
to get abortion

14:01.941 --> 14:06.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
services. It's a game-changer,
the decision
from the Supreme Court today,
which is why

14:06.045 --> 14:10.683 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we're excited about it, because
we have been
fighting these kind of sham laws
for years.

14:10.717 --> 14:15.621 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the Supreme Court has really
made clear
that you have got to have a
justification

14:15.655 --> 14:19.292 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
if you're going to regulate
abortion, and
that you have to make sure that
the burden

14:19.325 --> 14:24.330 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
doesn't overwhelm the
justification that the
law has, or it can't stand.

14:24.363 --> 14:28.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Steven Aden, was
this a game-changer?
Is this landmark, historical,
all those big

14:28.334 --> 14:30.203 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
words we have been using today?

14:30.236 --> 14:33.239 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN ADEN: It remains to be
seen whether
this is a one-off. As I said,
this was basically

14:33.272 --> 14:36.175 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the decision of one justice who
went the other
way.

14:36.209 --> 14:38.978 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Isn't that how most
things get
decided in the court?

14:39.011 --> 14:40.780 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
STEVEN ADEN: Unfortunately, yes.

14:40.813 --> 14:45.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what we will find out in
years to come
with I'm sure many cases like
this coming

14:45.051 --> 14:50.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
before the court is whether the
Supreme Court
is in earnest in making it more
difficult

14:50.757 --> 14:56.195 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for states to regulate abortion,
the same
way they do similar outpatient
medical providers.

14:56.229 --> 14:58.231 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's all Texas was really
trying to do.

14:58.264 --> 15:05.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the fact that it in fact
closed a number
of clinics says two things.
First, as the

15:05.304 --> 15:09.542 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
lead plaintiff in one of the
cases, Amy Hagstrom
Miller, said twice to The Wall
Street Journal,

15:09.575 --> 15:14.013 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
she's more concerned about
Planned Parenthood
closing her down, because
Planned Parenthood

15:14.046 --> 15:18.518 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is cornering the market for
abortion in Texas,
than about regulation itself.

15:18.551 --> 15:23.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So we don't know why those
clinics closed,
many of them. We just know that
they did.

15:23.723 --> 15:27.426 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that was the argument that
Texas made.
But, unfortunately, again, the
Supreme Court

15:27.460 --> 15:29.228 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
by one vote didn't accept that
argument.

15:29.262 --> 15:31.631 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: I want you to
respond to that.
And then I want to ask you about
that single-vote

15:31.664 --> 15:33.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
majority.

15:33.299 --> 15:35.134 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NANCY NORTHUP: Well, I think
really the decision
today is the response to that.

15:35.168 --> 15:39.405 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The court could not have been
clearer that
was no justification for these
laws. And this

15:39.438 --> 15:45.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is what we have been facing in
scores of laws
passed around the country. And
court after

15:45.244 --> 15:48.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
court after court in general
have blocked
them because they're not
justified. They see

15:48.881 --> 15:53.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
them for what they are, which is
an attempt
to do by the back door what you
can't by the

15:53.286 --> 15:56.222 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
front, which is ban abortion.

15:56.255 --> 16:01.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Supreme Court reiterated
today, as it
has for 40 years, women have a
right to make

16:01.227 --> 16:06.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the important personal decisions
for their
lives. And with this decision
today, the reason

16:06.299 --> 16:11.304 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it's so monumental is that it
protects for
the next generation of American
women the

16:11.337 --> 16:13.139 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
right to make these decisions
for themselves.

16:13.172 --> 16:16.876 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Let's talk about how
the decision
got made. You have mentioned a
couple of times,

16:16.909 --> 16:21.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Steven Aden, that Justice
Kennedy, is who
you're speaking of in this case,
decided basically

16:21.848 --> 16:23.816 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to tip the balance. Were you
surprised by
that?

16:23.850 --> 16:25.618 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
STEVEN ADEN: A little bit.

16:25.651 --> 16:29.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He has made no secret of his
antipathy for
abortion. He spoke strongly
against it the

16:29.889 --> 16:35.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
last time the Supreme Court made
a pronouncement
on the practice back in Gonzales
v. Carhart.

16:35.828 --> 16:40.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What is interesting to note
about this is,
when you talk about women making
decisions,

16:40.600 --> 16:46.873 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this law was upheld twice by two
Fifth Circuit
panels. Open those Fifth Circuit
panels were

16:46.906 --> 16:53.079 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
