the court, decided that law was
a no-go, imposed

17:02.321 --> 17:04.056 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
an undue burden, which is a
shame.

17:04.090 --> 17:07.693 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: What about that, the
idea that
one man writing for the court
turned this

17:07.727 --> 17:12.164 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
upside down, against the
interests of women?

17:12.198 --> 17:17.003 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NANCY NORTHUP: The Supreme Court
obviously
is -- five justices ruled today
in our favor.

17:17.036 --> 17:19.839 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the issue is not whether
it's men or women
sitting on the court.

17:19.872 --> 17:24.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Americans differ in their views
about abortion.
What's important and the courts
recognize

17:24.377 --> 17:30.383 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that, while people of good faith
can disagree
about abortion, the Constitution
protects

17:30.416 --> 17:34.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
our decisions that we make about
whether or
not to end a pregnancy, the
decisions about

17:34.687 --> 17:36.689 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
our family and our lives and our
health.

17:36.722 --> 17:42.361 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's what matters. So
people can make
their own decisions, but what
the court protects

17:42.395 --> 17:47.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
and the rule of law was
vindicated today was
that it is for women to make
these decisions.

17:47.767 --> 17:51.437 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's been true for over 40
years, and it
was reaffirmed again today in
this important

17:51.470 --> 17:52.939 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
case.

17:52.972 --> 17:54.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: That said, were you
surprised
by Justice Kennedy's decision?

17:54.774 --> 17:58.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NANCY NORTHUP: Justice Kennedy
was in the
majority in the Planned
Parenthood vs. Casey

17:58.978 --> 18:04.050 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
case, which was the last huge
abortion case
that set the standard that the
court interpreted

18:04.083 --> 18:05.885 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
today.

18:05.918 --> 18:09.155 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So Justice Kennedy was
consistent with the
decision, as the court was in
what they ruled

18:09.188 --> 18:10.923 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on 24 years ago.

18:10.957 --> 18:14.994 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Let me ask you both
briefly, is
this it? Is this over, or does
this fight

18:15.027 --> 18:16.762 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
continue in another way?

18:16.796 --> 18:19.999 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
STEVEN ADEN: I think it
continues in many
ways. The pro-life movement has
been winning

18:20.032 --> 18:25.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on all fronts. It lost today in
this one court,
but it's been winning in the
court of public

18:25.071 --> 18:30.543 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
opinion. It's been winning the
First Amendment
questions about access to
sidewalks in front

18:30.576 --> 18:32.411 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of abortion clinics.

18:32.445 --> 18:38.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
By and large, the -- in fact,
the abortion
rate today is the same as it was
in 1973,

18:38.050 --> 18:42.688 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the year Roe vs. Wade was
decided, which tells
me that the pro-life movement is
winning.

18:42.722 --> 18:45.591 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think we will continue to
win, regardless
of what the courts say, although
the fight

18:45.624 --> 18:46.892 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
will continue in the courts.

18:46.926 --> 18:49.028 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NANCY NORTHUP: We have a lot of
work ahead
of us.

18:49.061 --> 18:53.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are state laws that we're
going to get
overturned in the light of this
decision.

18:54.000 --> 18:58.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the momentum is on our side.
In fact,
seven in 10 Americans do support
that women

18:58.771 --> 19:02.274 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
